article.description: Sam Griffin had 13 points as UT Arlington beat Georgia State 70-62 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Griffin carries UT Arlington past Georgia St. 70-62
article.linkText: Griffin carries UT Arlington past Georgia St. 70-62
article.story: ARLINGTON, Texas -- Sam Griffin had 13 points as UT Arlington beat Georgia State 70-62 on Thursday night. Nicolas Elame had 12 points and eight rebounds for Texas-Arlington (13-15, 9-8 Sun Belt Conference), which earned its fourth consecutive home victory. David Azore added 11 points. Jabari Narcis had 10 points and three blocks. Georgia State totaled 27 second-half points, a season low for the team. Kane Williams had 21 points and seven rebounds for the Panthers (18-10, 11-6). Corey Allen added 12 points. Damon Wilson had nine rebounds. The Mavericks leveled the season series against the Panthers with the win. Georgia State defeated Texas-Arlington 83-77 on Dec. 19. Texas-Arlington takes on Georgia Southern at home on Saturday. Georgia State plays Texas State on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
